The '''Sisterhood Is Global Institute''' (SIGI) is an international non-governmental organization. For almost three decades, SIGI has been a consultant to the United Nations. 

SIGI was founded in 1984 by [[Robin Morgan]] and [[Simone de Beauvoir]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=McMahon|first1=Janet|title=Sisterhood Is Global Institute Presents Human Rights Manual at MEI|journal=Washington Report on Middle East Affairs|date=November 1997|volume=XI|issue=3|page=65|url=https://www.questia.com/read/1P3-509415171/sisterhood-is-global-institute-presents-human-rights|publisher=American Educational Trust{{Subscription required |via=[[Questia]]}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Delinda|first1=C.|title=Preventing Violence against Women in Muslim Societies|journal=Washington Report on Middle East Affairs|date=February 1999|volume=XII|issue=8|page=106|url=https://www.questia.com/read/1P3-509410341/preventing-violence-against-women-in-muslim-societies|publisher=American Educational Trust{{Subscription required |via=[[Questia]]}}}}</ref> A spinoff of "Sisterhood Is Global", SIGI was the "first international feminist [[think tank]]".{{sfn|Morgan|2007|p=18}}

